{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:sirach.14",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 14 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:1",
      "text": "Blessed is the man that hath not slipped with his mouth, and is not pricked with the multitude of sins.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:2",
      "text": "Blessed is he whose conscience hath not condemned him, and who is not fallen from his hope in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:3",
      "text": "Riches are not comely for a niggard: and what should an envious man do with money?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:4",
      "text": "He that gathereth by defrauding his own soul gathereth for others, that shall spend his goods riotously.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:5",
      "text": "He that is evil to himself, to whom will he be good? he shall not take pleasure in his goods.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:6",
      "text": "There is none worse than he that envieth himself; and this is a recompence of his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:7",
      "text": "And if he doeth good, he doeth it unwillingly; and at the last he will declare his wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:8",
      "text": "The envious man hath a wicked eye; he turneth away his face, and despiseth men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:9",
      "text": "A covetous man’s eye is not satisfied with his portion; and the iniquity of the wicked drieth up his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:10",
      "text": "A wicked eye envieth his bread, and he is a niggard at his table.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:11",
      "text": "My son, according to thy ability do good to thyself, and give the Lord his due offering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:12",
      "text": "Remember that death will not be long in coming, and that the covenant of the grave is not shewed unto thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:13",
      "text": "Do good unto thy friend before thou die, and according to thy ability stretch out thy hand and give to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:14",
      "text": "Defraud not thyself of the good day, and let not the part of a good desire overpass thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:15",
      "text": "Shalt thou not leave thy travails unto another? and thy labours to be divided by lot?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:16",
      "text": "Give, and take, and sanctify thy soul; for there is no seeking of dainties in the grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:17",
      "text": "All flesh waxeth old as a garment: for the covenant from the beginning is, Thou shalt die the death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:18",
      "text": "As of the green leaves on a thick tree, some fall, and some grow; so is the generation of flesh and blood, one cometh to an end, and another is born.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:19",
      "text": "Every work rotteth and consumeth away, and the worker thereof shall go withal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:20",
      "text": "Blessed is the man that doth meditate good things in wisdom, and that reasoneth of holy things by his understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:21",
      "text": "He that considereth her ways in his heart shall also have understanding in her secrets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:22",
      "text": "Go after her as one that traceth, and lie in wait in her ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:23",
      "text": "He that prieth in at her windows shall also hearken at her doors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:24",
      "text": "He that doth lodge near her house shall also fasten a pin in her walls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:25",
      "text": "He shall pitch his tent nigh unto her, and shall lodge in a lodging where good things are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:26",
      "text": "He shall set his children under her shelter, and shall lodge under her branches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:sirach.14.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 14:27",
      "text": "By her he shall be covered from heat, and in her glory shall he dwell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
